<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,1457,1884]" lastBlockId="9.[264,1323,284,470]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,451,1737,1763]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kaneshiro, K. Y." box="[462,671,1738,1764]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="79 - 83" refId="ref6354" refString="Kaneshiro, K. Y. (1969) The Drosophila crassifemur group of species in a new subgenus. University of Texas Publications, 6918, 79 - 83." type="journal article" year="1969">Kaneshiro (1969)</bibRefCitation>
recognized a single species group (
<taxonomicName authorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1111,1249,1738,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassifemur">
<emphasis box="[1111,1249,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">crassifemur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) containing two subgroups (
<taxonomicName authorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[550,689,1778,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassifemur">
<emphasis box="[550,689,1778,1803]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">crassifemur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[751,834,1778,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasalis">
<emphasis box="[751,834,1778,1803]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">nasalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) within this subgenus. We will leave all taxonomic ranks below the level of subgenus intact. The polytene chromosome of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[342,534,1858,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Engiscaptomyza">
<emphasis box="[342,534,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Engiscaptomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, unlike those of the remainder of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hardy" authorityYear="1850" box="[1064,1204,1858,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1064,1204,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scaptomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are large and easy to decipher. 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoon, J. S. &amp; Resch K. &amp; Wheeler, M. R. &amp; Richardson, R. H." box="[520,734,284,310]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="249 - 256" refId="ref6778" refString="Yoon, J. S., Resch K., Wheeler, M. R., &amp; Richardson, R. H. (1975) Evolution in Hawaiian Drosophilidae: chromosomal phylogeny of the Drosophila crassifemur complex. Evolution, 29, 249 - 256." type="journal article" year="1975">Yoon et al. (1975)</bibRefCitation>
examined the phylogenetic relationships between four species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[621,813,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Engiscaptomyza">
<emphasis box="[621,813,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Engiscaptomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using polytene chromosome banding patterns. Their work suggests that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[631,748,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[631,748,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion box="[763,860,364,390]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Hawai‘i</collectingRegion>
) and 
