<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
14. Front femur swollen, rufous in color; scutellum with additional setulae inserted on margin between anterior and posterior scutellar setae; ovipositor blunt, with ca. 5 elongate setulae along margin. Maui, Moloka‘i ............................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grimshaw)" authorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="O’Grady &amp; Bonacum &amp; Desalle &amp; Val" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1035,1323,1204,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Scaptomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassifemur">
